      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "ci: skip macOS shards for docs-only changes",
        "body": "## Summary\n- add a cheap `changes` job that classifies whether a PR/push can skip macOS Swift test shards\n- skip `swift-test-macos` only for docs/Markdown-only changes\n- allow the aggregate gate to pass when macOS shards are intentionally skipped\n\n## Why\nThe current CI still requests four macOS runners for docs-only PRs. macOS queue time is the main remaining source of pending checks, so avoiding those shards for non-code changes reduces queue pressure without weakening validation for source, tests, scripts, workflow, or app localization changes.\n\n## Safety\n- Source, tests, scripts, workflow, package, and app localization changes still require macOS Swift tests.\n- Empty or unavailable base diff falls back to running macOS tests.\n- The aggregate job accepts only `success` or intentional `skipped` for the macOS matrix.\n\n## Validation\n- workflow YAML parsed with `yaml.safe_load`\n- `bash -n Scripts/ci_macos_test_gate.sh`\n- `git diff --check`\n- docs/Markdown sample (`README.md`, `docs/index.html`, `docs/releasing-homebrew.md`) prints: `Skipping macOS Swift tests for docs/Markdown-only changes.`\n- source sample (`Sources/CodexBar/MenuCardView.swift`) prints: `macOS Swift tests required for this change set.`\n- app localization sample (`Sources/CodexBar/Resources/en.lproj/Localizable.strings`) prints: `macOS Swift tests required for this change set.`\n- CI/scripts sample (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`, `Scripts/lint.sh`) prints: `macOS Swift tests required for this change set.`\n- empty changed-path list conservatively prints: `macOS Swift tests required for this change set.`\n- `GITHUB_OUTPUT` emits `macos-tests=false` for docs-only sample\n\n## GitHub Actions proof\nDocs-only proof PR: https://github.com/Yuxin-Qiao/CodexBar/pull/3\n\nAt run https://github.com/Yuxin-Qiao/CodexBar/actions/runs/27831467301:\n- `changes`: success\n- `swift-test-macos`: skipped\n- `lint-build-test`: success\n- `lint`: success\n\nThis proof PR targets the branch from this PR and changes only `docs/ci-path-gate-proof.md`, so it exercises the docs-only path that this PR is designed to optimize.\n",
